layers.nm: Hi! So...you’re stuck! I remember when I was stuck with React... React can be a bit difficult to learn! One thing that really helped me, was to take the weekends to try and build a React app that implemented the material that was taught during the week!   So basically, one week I didn’t understand APIs and how to make the calls and setting states. So I built a movie app over the weekend! I used an API called tmdb and so I spent the weekend playing with that api. I learned how to read the response. That apis are typically returned as an array of objects... Which means, you can use Javascript array methods! So like map, filter, foreach, all that kind of stuff!   I learned that when I get responses back from the api that I have to set my state to an empty object first! And also, I can name my state anything. So like foobar: [ ]. And whenever I use foobar, that’s basically allowing me to access that data that was set when I made the api request!

So I built a movie app over the weekend! I used an API called tmdb and so I spent the weekend playing with that api. I learned how to read the response. That apis are typically returned as an array of objects... Which means, you can use Javascript array methods! So like map, filter, foreach, all that kind of stuff! I learned that when I get responses back from the api that I have to set my state to an empty object first! And also, I can name my state anything. So like foobar: [ ]. And whenever I use foobar, that’s basically allowing me to access that data that was set when I made the api request!
